races.description:
Described as bipedal canine-like humanoids, the Lucario have garnered a reputation for being fiercesome melee fighters as well as coming across as arrogant and aloof in their few dealings with humanlikes.

Widely seen as violent isolationists, more patient and gifted individuals would find the Lucario more welcoming, having a natural sense of justice and trusting those who across time earned their loyalty. It is from these exchanges that Lucario have been discovered to be telepathic, as well as able to sense and manipulate energies from all lifeforms, dubbed as 'Aura' by the Lucario themsleves.

The genesis of the Lucario are a mystery, even to the Lucario themselves. Fragmentary accounts as well as DNA analysis of Lucario volunteers point to them being the product of glitterworld genetic engineering, likely for security or entertainment purposes. How they became sentient or developed their telepathic abilites remains mysterious, though many stories tell of the Lucario (sometimes alongside their creators) travelling in ancient space vessels seeking a new home among the stars.
races.name: lucario

races.description:
Once mistaken as a seperate species, Riolu are actually the juvenile form of the Lucario.

Drawing from tales and legends concerning glitterworld technologies as well as the experiences imparted from the Lucario, it is now believed that some Lucario were bred specifically to retain their youthful features and obedient loyalty, giving rise to a sub-species who are smaller, weaker and more attractive. Despite this, the Riolu still retain the determination and zeal of their parent bretheren.
races.name: riolu

races.description:
As formidable as the Lucario are, more recent rumours point to several Lucario individuals seeking to hone their skills and strengh even beyond that known.

Across the Rimworlds there has been at least one Lucario taking a long and difficult journey to a site rumoured to hold immense power. Those that succeed return transformed, augmented with power and abilites previously thought impossible. It also heralds their first step to becoming powerful leaders within their society, often measured in the aggression they unleash.

While fortunately few in number, Mega Lucario have been known to be resilient beyond measure and even more ruthless in battle, sometimes able to engage half a dozen soldiers all alone. Only the most veteran of soldiers or overwhelming firepower would stand a chance to defeat such an opponent.
races.name: mega lucario

The Rockmen, as they have been nicknamed by humans, are called so because of their unique skin which according to scientific experiments can be nearly as hard and rugged as solid rock. Additionally, the Rockmen are extremely well conditioned and physically strong to compensate for their thick rock-like skin, giving them an astounding resilience. As a result of their physical attributes, the Rockmen have evolved throughout their race's existence into a warrior race which values personal strength and martial prowess over nearly everything else.
While the Rockmen are generally not an adventurous race, and can only be consistently located within their own territories' borders, the Rockmen are liable to open fire on any ship they encounter that they aren't familiar with. Still, there are always exceptions to the rule, and having Rockmen crew can be very beneficial. Also, from random occurrences, some Rockmen seem to be quite religious.

Togruta were also distinguished by montrals, large hollow horn-like projections from the top of their heads, that gave the species a form of passive echolocation. In order to protect themselves from dangerous predators, and to hunt their own prey, Togruta banded together in tribes and relied on their natural pigmentation to disrupt and confuse slow-witted beasts. Togruta worked well in large groups, and individualism was seen as abnormal within their culture, although it was also a necessary quality in leaders.

races.description:
These twisted rat-like creatures call themselves the Skaven, the Children Of The Horned Rat. Others call them ratmen, rat-spawn, or thaggoraki. They are a malevolent and diabolical race of large humanoid rat-creatures. Malevolent and numerous, they bring corruption and ruin to the farthest corners of the Old World. Each Skaven down to the individual is cruel, petty, devious, sly, and in almost every way a twisted reflection on all of mankind's flaws. They have no concept of loyalty, humility, or empathy. The only things that guide skaven behaviour are hunger, ego, and most importantly: fear.

Hunger plagues daily skaven life far more than it does to almost any other race in the Old World, second only to the insatiable Ogres of the Mountains Of Mourn. This hunger largely fuels their incredibly fast metabolism, letting them move and react at inhuman speeds...but it comes at a cost. If permitted to eat their fill, a single skaven will consume an amount of meat rivalling their own body weight in a single day. Malnutrition and starvation runs rampant in all of skavendom as they struggle to feed their teeming ranks, especially ones with such voracious appetites and needs that they would perish from starvation in a matter of three days. This is known by the skaven as the Black Hunger, a blessing and a curse to be both feared and exploited. Skaven magic can even tap into this hunger to send swathes of skaven into an inhuman frenzy.

Ego drives and bends much of skavendom to the twisted desires of the powerful few. Each skaven is born with delusions of power and ambition, believing they are the one chosen rat in all of Skavendom and destined for greatness. A whole species of ambitious, conniving, psychopathic ratkin all vying for total world domination.

Most importantly, the skaven are driven largely by fear. Fear is the primary tool of power in skavendom, with powerful skaven threatening their lackeys to action instead of inspiring them. Fear drives trade, action, politics, intrigue, diplomacy, every single aspect of their society. It's so omnipresent that the skaven have developed musk glands that, when squirted, create a foul-smelling odour that triggers their primal fight-or-flight instincts.
races.name: skaven

They are aggressive by nature, and are given to overt displays of prowess in order to intimidate those around them. These stronger skaven are most commonly trained to join the ranks of the Stormvermin, but every clan finds another way to employ them. Clan Eshin trains their black-furs in martial arts and tactics, combining their natural brawn with the speed of a Gutter Runner as part of the Eshin Triads. They have long muscular tongues with which they scoop mollusks and lesser amphibians from the Naboo swamps. While most spacefarers would dismiss Gungans as primitives, they have developed an advanced technology.
races.name: Gungan

races.description:
The most common and adaptable Ursine species, it is hard to truly describe their unique traits as what makes them unique is that they tread the middle ground, able to adapt to almost any environment and situation. Researchers would be quick to point out there are technically many further sub groups including such ursines as the Grizzly and Kodiak. But most still put these in the general Brown ursine group as they are just the small adaptations that have cropped up because of their environment, but are still largely similar.
Prior to large tribes forming these Ursines were quite solitary, preferring to live alone. But with the rise of the Ursine tribes it is now not uncommon to see Brown Ursines make up the majority of a tribe's population.
races.name: Brown Ursin

races.description:
Long thought extinct by those in the core worlds, out here in the rim the practically Legendary Cave Ursine still wanders and makes its home. These typically massive Ursine are rare on many worlds, though some still have larger populations. Wherever the Cave Ursine joins a tribe with its kin, it often finds itself in the position of mighty warrior or even leadership positions because of its sheer might, something the peaceful tribes value greatly to ward off potential aggressors and defend them from the plethora of threats out here in the rim.
Though their genes have now mixed with their other kin in the larger tribes, the Cave Ursine is thought to be the progenitor of all Ursine kind, and a pure blooded Cave Ursine will easily tower over their fellow brothers and sisters of other sub groups. These two factors have given some of their kind practically demi-god status in certain societies. Though in the grand scheme such worship is quite rare.
races.name: Cave Ursin

races.description:
Amongst the smallest of the Ursines, the Luna Ursine are, perhaps unsurprisingly, typically the most timid of the lot. In a society that although not aggressive still values strength for the safety of the tribe, these are often on the lower ends of the hierarchy. Though it is always worth noting as the different subspecies have mixed together this disparity in size has been reduced drastically in comparison to before. 
The Luna Ursine are good scavengers, and surprisingly clever amongst their kin, as they often have to be to make up for being physically smaller. Although adaptable, they do share a habitat preference with their animal likeness in that they are fond of forested areas that are relatively inaccessible. A preference guided by survival more so than anything.
As the name would suggest it is at the very least believed by the Ursine that this subspecies have an innate connection with the moon, or moons depending on the rimworld. This has lended them some favorability despite their size, and some of them choose to take up roles of spiritual guidance because of it.
races.name: Luna Ursin

races.description:
Though originally these highly specialized Ursine had a very particular diet of almost only bamboo, as they have evolved, traveled, and gathered with their fellow Ursine kin the Pandas have been able to grow out of this habit and their bodies more used to other diets.
Generally Pandas are incredibly solitary, even in large tribes it is not uncommon to see these individuals construct their homes on the outskirts of settlements to give them more privacy.
This behavior, as well as being very docile and single minded, have lended them a certain leaning towards roles of spiritual guidance, like monks, druids, shamans, or other such roles. Where they are one of the primary advocates of peaceful behavior in the tribe.
But do not think these defenseless creatures, if provocet sufficiently you will find they are still very much Ursine at their core, and will not hesitate to maul someone overstepping their boundaries if they consider it necessary.
races.name: Panda Ursin

races.description:
Though often seen by outsiders as amongst the most aggressive of the Ursines, the reality is that they are actually quite passive, like their other kin they prefer to avoid conflict when possible. They’re not very territorial either and will often not be bothered when others are around. however they are adept hunters, because they evolved and adapted to arctic areas with very little other food sources, in their natural habitat they are entirely carnivorous. And have become excellent ambush hunters to survive.
This has made them excellent hunters in tribes that eat meat, or guards/skirmishers in those that don’t. Which is why they are often seen as more aggressive.
As could probably be expected given their nature, the Polar ursine are typically larger than most other Ursine races. Though such differences have been somewhat mitigated as they have intermingled with their other kin to form larger tribes.
races.name: Polar Ursin
